joelib2.io.types
Class Smiles

java.lang.Object
  joelib2.io.types.Smiles
All Implemented Interfaces:
MoleculeFileExport, MoleculeFileImport, MoleculeFileIO
public class Smiles
extends Object
implements MoleculeFileIO

Reader/Writer for Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System (SMILES) files.

The SMILES import/export has some additional parameters which were defined in the BasicPropertyHolder. The BasicResourceLoader loads the joelib2.properties file for default.

Java property Description Default value
joelib2.io.types.Smiles.lineStructure Line structure of the SMILES in the file/inputstream. SMILES and TITLE are fixed code words, which represents the SMILES molecule and the molecule title. All other descriptor names, which represents native descriptor values, are allowed. SMILES|TITLE
joelib2.io.types.Smiles.lineStructure.delimiter The delimiter used in the line structure definition. |
joelib2.io.types.Smiles.lineStructure.input.delimiter The input delimiter in the file/inputstream between line entries. \ \t\n\r
joelib2.io.types.Smiles.lineStructure.output.delimiter The output delimiter in the file/outputstream between line entries. \ \

See Also:
BasicPropertyHolder, BasicResourceLoader
